    <stitle>10 SPEED TRANSMISSIONS EATON RTLO SERIES - REMOVE - COUNTERSHAFT ASSEMBLY (REAR CASE)</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="remove" graphiccount="3">
        <title>COUNTERSHAFT ASSEMBLY (REAR CASE)</title>
        <para>For ease of disassembly, mount the auxiliary section upright in a vise.</para>
        <para>Both countershafts are removed the same.</para>
        <para>As the countershaft strap is removed, the countershaft can fall.</para>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Temporarily install a output yoke on the output shaft (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1301761">Figure 61</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1301761" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1301761" filename="../figg13/G1301761.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 61. Breaker Bar</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">To keep the output shaft from turning, insert a breaker bar (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1301761">Figure 61</hotlnk>).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Loosen the 15/16" bolt and retainer on the output shaft. Do not remove the bolt. Remove the
                bar and output yoke (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1301762">Figure 62</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1301762" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1301762" filename="../figg13/G1301762.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 62. Remove Bar and Output Yoke</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Use a soft bar and maul to drive the countershaft forward far enough to partially unseat the
                bearing.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Support the auxiliary countershaft while removing the auxiliary countershaft retaining strap
                (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1301763">Figure 63</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1301763" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1301763" filename="../figg13/G1301763.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 63. Auxiliary Countershaft</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the auxiliary countershaft (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1301763">Figure 63</hotlnk>).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Secure the countershaft assemblies in a vise and remove both the front and rear bearings
                with a bearing puller and separator jaws.
            </para>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
